               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Sayfa malakot “Sword of Divinity” (fols. 2r-5v)&#xD; II) Ǝgziʾabǝḥer
                     za-bǝrhānāt ʾǝgziʾabǝḥer za-śǝlṭānāt... “God of Lights, God of Powers...”
                     (Prayer to Lord) (fols. 6r-8v, 53r) &#xD; III) Ḥaḍurä masqal “Rampart of the
                     Cross” (fols. 9r-52v)&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I:</note>
                     <note>- Cp. the text in S. GREBAUT, “La prière Sayfa malakot”, Aethiopica 4
                        (1936), 1-6). Cp. also Ms. JRyM 22, <locus from="31r" to="40v">31r-40v</locus> (StrJRyM 65).</note>
                     <note>Text II:</note>
                     <note>- Cp. “Ǝgziʾabǝḥer za-bǝrhānāt”, EAE II, 249, and ChRep 349, n<locus target="#363">363</locus>.</note>
                     <note>- The text is interrupted on <locus target="#8v">8v</locus>, and
                        continues on <locus target="#53r">53r</locus>. On <locus target="#8v">8v</locus>, the text ends with the words: ሀሎ፡ በተፍጻሜቱ፨ “(the writing) is
                        at the end” (written in a frame). The text is introduced on <locus target="#53r">53r</locus> by the words: ዝኒ፡ ዘተረፈ “This is what
                        remains”.</note>
                     <note>Text III:</note>
                     <note>- Cp. the text in D. LIFCHITZ, Textes éthiopiens magico-religieux, Paris
                        1940 (Travaux et Mémoires de l’Institut d’Ethnologie 38),<ref type="mss" corresp="ES92146">92-146</ref>. It is the version (incipit: በስመ፡’’… አአትብ፡
                        ገጽየ፡ ወእትነሣእ፡ በስመ፡ ፫አስማት፡ ነሢእየ፡ እትመረጐዝ፡…) which should not be confused with
                        the text “Prayer for the Rampart of the Cross” (incipit: ጸሎተ፡ በእንተ፡ ሐፁረ፡
                        መስቀል፡ ዘጸሐፈ፡ ኤርምያስ፡ ነቢይ፡…; cp. S. GREBAUT, “Litanies de la Croix”, Aethiopica
                        4 (1935), 187-90).</note>
                     <note>Cp. also “Ḥaṣurä masqal”, EAE II, 1045-46.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Some supplication formulas are dedicated to an individual for whom the
                        first person, with the word እገሌ “certain”, is used: አነ፡ ገብርከ፡ እገሌ፡ (<locus target="#21v">21v</locus>) ሊተ፡ ለገብርከ፡ እገሌ፡ (e.g., <locus target="#19v">19v</locus>, 23v).</note>
                  </msItem>
